Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic Party(LDP) on Tuesdayhose former Finance Minister Noboru Takeshitato be the next prime minister, replacing Yasuhiro Nakasonewhose term ends on October 30.    LDP officials told Reuters the choice was made by Nakasoneafter Takeshita and two other contenders failed in marathonclosed-door meetings to agree who should be Japan's nextleader.    They were vying for the presidency of the LDP, a post whichautomatically carries with it the premiership by virtue of theparty's parliamentary majority. Reuter&#3;